[In the past 24 hours, India (256 947), Turkey (55 149), the USA (51 650), and Brazil (34 642), have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 10 153 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 17 Apr 2021 to late 18 Apr 2021). Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (9 countries) include India, Turkey, the USA, Brazil, Iran (24 346), Argentina (20 461), Columbia (14 189), Germany (13 417), and Canada (10 275). A total of 51 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 24 of the 51 countries are from the European region, 9 are from the Americas region, 8 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 3 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 12.2%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 0.86%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 3.4% decrease in daily reported cases and 13.2% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily total is approximately 700 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours, with over 142.69 million cumulative reported cases and over 3.04 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA

